 WHITE RIVER – June Dreyer (29) has still not been found. White River SAPS spokesman, Sgt Cynthia Mbokodo confirmed that police are still investigating her disappearance. ALSO READ: White River mom missing since January Damien Crous, who is the father of Dreyer’s one-year-old, dropped her off to do shopping in White River that day. “I gave her R800 and she put the money in her bra, as she did not have her handbag. When I got home I waited for her to call. Then I saw her phone was in the house, on a charger,” he said.
Dreyer was last seen wearing black shorts, a striped vest and flip-flops. She has a tattoo on her left foot. Crous reported Dreyer missing to the police on February 10. The organisation Pink Ladies sent out a national alert concerning her disappearance. Mbokodo said there was no new information regarding the missing person’s case. Basil Anthony, father of Marvin Anthony (34), has confirmed he was found on Saturday. Basil went missing on February 16 in Nelsville. His father confirmed that he now is safely home. Anyone with any information regarding Dreyer can contact the investigating officer, Det PX Ngobe on 073-306-1140 or
060-606-5279.